user.name: K-tech Innovation Hub NASSCOM
user.description:
K-TECH INNOVATION HUB BY NASSCOM :

Overview:

The Government of Karnataka in line with its i4 policy has set up a K-Tech Innovation Hub at NASSCOM Diamond District, Old Airport Road, Domlur, Bengaluru. The facility has been fully set up and has been operational since 2013. K-Tech Innovation Hub is housed in the premises of Diamond District, Old Airport Road, Bengaluru. It is spread over an area of 37,000 sq. ft. and has a seating capacity of 350 with a 100% power backup, leased internet line, a vibrant ambiance, Conference room with AV facility, over 10 meeting rooms, cafeteria and housekeeping facilities. The facility offers subsidized incubation space which will help the Start-ups to make use of the ecosystem and in turn help the companies which are in their nascent stages to attract angel investors, VC’s and enterprises to play a major role in Bengaluru and helping more such Start-ups to thrive and succeed. They offer various services for e.g. providing physical workspace (Plug & Play), Support Services (HR/Legal/Accounting etc.), access to network of investors, mentors, and industry experts etc., access to Startup Kits etc. besides the subsidised seat rentals

user.name: Gopalakrishnan-Deshpande Centre for Innovation & Entrepreneurship
user.description: GDC is an alumni-funded initiative set up at IIT Madras. Our charter is to work with faculty, researchers, students, and alumni of all STEM colleges in India who wish to commercialise their science-based research by way of start-ups to create impact at scale in society. We work with early-stage, deep-tech startup ideas (typically about TRL3) and endeavour to help the founders move up to TRL6. Through our highly acclaimed programs, I-NCUBATE and I-NSPIRE, we have worked with nearly 600 researchers and entrepreneurs from nearly 125 start-ups from nearly 20 academic institutions. I-NCUBATE and I-NSPIRE are highly transformative programs and all participants experience a dramatic transformation in their capabilities, knowledge, and entrpreneurial quotient. See a promo video at https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=MkFdpYztED0

portfolios.brief: Tan90 is an energy efficient, green, cost effective enabler of refrigerated transport from farm to fork, providing portable, scalable and modular solutions, to increase shelf life of perishables. We provide end-to-end coverage from farm to fork, serving the hitherto un-served, unorganized primary producers, on the other hand and serving relatively organized intermediaries and end suppliers with lower capital cost and lower operating expenditure

Waste Chakra is a clean tech company specialized in manufacturing of decentralized plastic pyrolysis machines. Our machines convert plastic waste to commercial fuel oil, facilitating sustainable plastic waste management. Our compact machines make sure plastic waste can be treated from your backyard.

At Solinas, we build inline inspection robotic technologies for critical pipeline infrastructure to detect existing defects and also prevent failures, maximising the lifespan of assets. We serve O&G, Petrochemical, Power plants, Water, Sanitation and Process Industries.

VayuJal Technologies Pvt. Ltd. is an Indian company that aims to alleviate the global water shortage crisis through the development and manufacturing of Atmospheric Water Generators (AWGs). We started in 2016 and our AWGs were designed to be an affordable water extraction solution that was also environmentally sustainable to quench the thirst of millions. We are incubated by IIT Madras Research Center and are part of their ‘Water for the Future’ initiative.

user.name: AFBIC IITKGP
user.description:
Agri-Food Business Incubation Centre IIT Kharagpur (AFBIC IIT KGP) is an innovation and agripreneurship cell for supporting agribusiness incubation by exploring technological innovations for venture creation in agriculture and allied fields. It is aimed at strengthening start-up ecosystem in Agri-food and allied sectors to promote Agripreneurship by facilitating access to technology, domain experts and grant-in-aid for product and process innovation. The centre has been established under RKVY-RAFTAAR program  supported by Ministry of Agriculture and Farmers Welfare, Govt. of India. The Agricultural and Food Engineering dept, IIT Kharagpur is entrusted with the responsibility of creating necessary infrastructure for mentoring and nurturing Agri-entrepreneurs from the ideation to successful commercialisation phases under this centre. The successful startups from the program will be empowered with technological and business acumen who will be the torchbearers for financial independence, job creation and in mentoring and motivating like-spirited entrepreneurs in rural and urban areas.


RKVY-RAFTAAR (Rashtriya Krishi Vikas Yojana – Remunerative Approaches for Agriculture and Allied Sectors Rejuvenation ) is a unique scheme of Ministry of Agriculture and Farmers’ Welfare, Government of India, (MoA & FW). RKVY-RAFTAAR aims at making farming a remunerative economic activity through strengthening the farmers’ effort, risk mitigation and promoting agri-business entrepreneurship.

RKVY-RAFTAAR supports agribusiness incubation by tapping innovations and technologies for venture creation in agriculture.


AFBIC, IIT KGP as a R-ABI aims to support agri-food business entrepreneurs in product development, brand building and advertising, pricing and marketing of the product, technological improvements, IP protection and process optimization. In this process, incubation facilities and expertise already available with IIT KGP are being utilized. The focus of AFBIC is to create a favourable environment for the growth of the start-ups from where they can explore new opportunities related to their area for further upscaling. AFBIC through its two programmes “Agri Orientation Program(AOP)” and “Agri-Startup Incubation Program(AIP)” is providing funding support in the form of Grant-in-aid of upto INR 5 Lakhs and INR 25 Lakhs respectively.

user.description:
At Startupvisors, we help startups or individual in taking their startup/idea to a successful venture. We believe in actions that's the reason we do not provide any theoretical course. We help startups in converting an idea into a scalable business with our virtual incubation where we help entrepreneurs with market validation, product development, business planning and strategies to be implemented in order to get on the road of success with the help of our mentorship and funding network span over a period of 6 months.


We provide ongoing virtual incubation where we select startups based on their idea. Once selected, We along with the team of experts provide weekly online sessions guiding entrepreneurs right from helping them articulating their business idea to taking it to execution.


Incubation program runs for 6 months entails idea validation, understanding business eco-system, market research understanding value proposition of the business, customer research, technology enablement, revenue model, go to market strategy and then scaling the business.


In the program, we help them in creating a business pitch along with multiple mock pitch sessions for raising funds by connecting the startups with various investors and angel networks through our demo day.


Startupvisors aim to support and convert these business ideas to "Startup Success stories" by providing them all possible resources.

user.name: Samruddhi TBI Foundation
user.description:
1. Brief Introduction: 

 

It is a fact that, a quality and successful incubation needs interweaving of all the stakeholders including academic institutions, governments, industrial bodies, corporate, research labs and other business incubators, Samrudhhi TBI (STBI) Foundation Sangli, is positioning itself to create a unique example in the antiquity of incubation. The strength of STBI is not only the achievements of its founders as successful entrepreneurs themselves but it is in its outstanding incubation operations management and self-sustainable business model.   

 

With cluster of partnership / Association with more than 25 academic institutes (Engineering and Technology, Design, Management, Law, Commerce) supported by successful manufacturing Industry like “Samruddhi Industries Limited” and leading industries in the region, STBI is aiming to become most successful and efficient incubation centre in India. Its “jugaadfunda.com”, the Incubation and SME support portal (Developed by Regional Laboratory for Applied Research and Development) is positioning to interconnect academic institutions, government, industrial bodies, corporate, research labs and other business incubators creating truly unified eco-system for nurturing entrepreneurs.  With thrust area of “Product Design and Manufacturing”, it is positioning strongly to support innovators and SME across the region.  

 

With total available dedicated space of more than 3000 sq. feet, STBI has already graduated 3 start-up companies in the manufacturing sector. With ample awareness of start-up eco system in Tier-I cities, true success and expected outcome of start-up India policy can be achieved when this movement shall penetrate Tier-II and Tier-III cities where ample grass root innovations are awaiting adequate support.  

 

Sangli, Kolhapur Districts in western, Maharashtra with manufacturing SME turnover of more than 12000 Cr, more than 1200 small and medium manufacturing industries, and more than 180 academic institutes is right place to initiate sectoral incubation centre supporting “Engineering Product Design and Manufacturing”  

 

We at STBI are committed to bring in the change. We strongly appeal the Start-Up India to recognise our honest efforts and empower us to multiply our efforts to contribute in achieving objectives of Stat-Up India policy. We intensely feel we deserve the maximum possible support to strengthen our sincere efforts. 

 

 

 

Manish M Patil 

Omprakash Malu 

Founder Directors 

Samruddhi TBI Foundation
